01:53:27.940 --> 01:53:35.940
Presently, I want to ask about you had mentioned during the break that Dr. King's speech

01:53:35.940 --> 01:53:45.940
at Riverside Church really drew your attention to him and that kind of new wire sense,

01:53:45.940 --> 01:53:48.940
I think, as the 60s were moving on.

01:53:48.940 --> 01:53:49.940
Sure.

01:53:49.940 --> 01:53:54.940
Well, he really blended all these issues.

01:53:54.940 --> 01:53:58.940
I mean, there was a racial issues, civil rights.

01:53:58.940 --> 01:54:01.940
There was the economic.

01:54:01.940 --> 01:54:05.940
We did go to the people's, well, that was after his death.

01:54:05.940 --> 01:54:10.940
But we went to the poor people's march as well.

01:54:10.940 --> 01:54:13.940
And the war.

01:54:13.940 --> 01:54:15.940
And what was it?

01:54:15.940 --> 01:54:21.940
Muhammad Ali said, no nigger ever, no Vietnamese ever called me nigger.

01:54:21.940 --> 01:54:29.940
And I think, you know, that this was just,

01:54:29.940 --> 01:54:34.940
that war was on so many levels wrong.

01:54:34.940 --> 01:54:43.940
I mean, it was wrong for us to move in to take over for the French after Jenbin Fou.

01:54:43.940 --> 01:54:49.940
And it was wrong for the poverty draft.

01:54:49.940 --> 01:54:53.940
It was not, it was even though it was everybody draft.

01:54:53.940 --> 01:54:58.940
The other people who could get out of it did get out of it.

01:54:58.940 --> 01:55:05.940
And the economic impact on this country, just as same as we're seeing right now.

01:55:05.940 --> 01:55:13.940
So we have a poverty draft now, and we have this country short-changing the needs of its own people.

01:55:13.940 --> 01:55:22.940
So Dr. King, I mean, listening to that speech this spring, I heard it again on the radio,

01:55:22.940 --> 01:55:28.940
which really made me happy. It was on our Albany Station NPR.

01:55:28.940 --> 01:55:33.940
It just, you know, really was so deep.

01:55:33.940 --> 01:55:37.940
And so he's been called a philosopher, what is it?

01:55:37.940 --> 01:55:41.940
An activist philosopher, Dr. King.

01:55:41.940 --> 01:55:46.940
And most philosophers are not sort of as activists, but he certainly was.

01:55:46.940 --> 01:55:53.940
Some people would maybe not call him a philosopher, but I would.

01:55:53.940 --> 01:55:58.940
And I also had great respect for Malcolm X.

01:55:58.940 --> 01:56:03.940
We just recently went to the memorial of the author of the new book about him.

01:56:03.940 --> 01:56:05.940
And I'm not terrible.

01:56:05.940 --> 01:56:06.940
I'm not terrible.

01:56:06.940 --> 01:56:07.940
I'm not terrible.

01:56:07.940 --> 01:56:08.940
I'm not terrible.

01:56:08.940 --> 01:56:09.940
I'm not terrible.

01:56:09.940 --> 01:56:10.940
I'm not terrible.

01:56:10.940 --> 01:56:11.940
I'm not terrible.

01:56:11.940 --> 01:56:12.940
I'm not terrible.

01:56:12.940 --> 01:56:13.940
I'm not terrible.

01:56:13.940 --> 01:56:14.940
I'm not terrible.

01:56:14.940 --> 01:56:26.940
And so, you know, this, any, and I know in his speech, grassroots speech, you know,

01:56:26.940 --> 01:56:29.940
he ridiculed the March on Washington and so on.

01:56:29.940 --> 01:56:31.940
I could understand that.

01:56:31.940 --> 01:56:33.940
I could understand where he was coming from.

01:56:33.940 --> 01:56:37.940
It didn't make him my enemy for that.

01:56:37.940 --> 01:56:43.940
And I think he brought a lot of understanding to the, you know,

01:56:43.940 --> 01:56:47.940
the people who are really disenfranchised in this country.

01:56:47.940 --> 01:56:53.940
So, the combination of these two great leaders, we don't have that today.

01:56:53.940 --> 01:57:02.940
But what we really are missing is a mass movement that created them rather than that we need leaders.

01:57:02.940 --> 01:57:05.940
We need the mass movement.

01:57:05.940 --> 01:57:08.940
And we're not having it.

01:57:08.940 --> 01:57:09.940
Try as I may.

01:57:09.940 --> 01:57:11.940
I'm trying to get those seniors.

01:57:11.940 --> 01:57:14.940
I'm trying to get those seniors.

01:57:14.940 --> 01:57:15.940
I'm trying to get those seniors.

01:57:15.940 --> 01:57:27.940
So much so that I know, so much so the both of you that you have been, recent years, been honored yet again for your ongoing commitments and contributions in these ways.

01:57:27.940 --> 01:57:40.940
Let me ask two about the, about the long experience now, the lovely long experience of 60 or I don't know your anniversary date, but maybe 61 years of, maybe, 19.

01:57:40.940 --> 01:57:41.940
61.

